Commercial Bank of Africa Raises Kenyan Loan Rate for Second Time in Month

-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 
2011-07-20T04:06:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/commercial-bank-of-africa-raises-kenyan-loan-rate-for-second-time-in-month.html
Commercial Bank of Africa Ltd., a
Kenyan lender, raised its base lending rate to 15 percent from
14.5 percent, the second increase in a month.  The higher cost of borrowing is effective from Aug. 1, the
Nairobi-based bank said in a statement published in the Standard
newspaper today. On June 14, the bank announced it had lifted
its loan rate to 14.5 percent from 13 percent with effect from
July 11.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  